articles.title: Sudan army, paramilitaries clash: African Union Commission calls for ceasefire - WION
articles.description: Sounds of explosions and gunfire were heard across the Sudanese capital of Khartoum, on Saturday (April 15), amid clashes between the country’s army and the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) paramilitary.
articles.content: Witnesses reported confrontations and loud explosions and gunfire near a base held by the RSF in south Khartoum, said a report by AFP, whose reporters heard gunfire near Khartoum airport as well in n… [+781 chars]
